<p>Every HoloVault listing includes honest condition notes and photos so you know exactly what you are buying before checkout.</p>

<h2>How we grade</h2>
<p>We use common collector terms where stated, including:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>NM (Near Mint)</strong> — minimal wear, sharp corners and edges</li>
  <li><strong>LP (Lightly Played)</strong> — light wear visible on close inspection</li>
  <li><strong>MP (Moderately Played)</strong> — noticeable wear but still collectible</li>
  <li><strong>HP (Heavily Played)</strong> — significant wear; priced accordingly</li>
</ul>

<h2>What we photograph</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Front of card in sleeve where possible</li>
  <li>Back when condition is relevant</li>
  <li>Close-ups of edges, corners, or surface issues when present</li>
  <li>Pattern or language variants (e.g. Poke Ball, Master Ball, CN) in the title</li>
</ul>

<h2>Before you order</h2>
<p>Please read the listing title, description, and photos carefully. HoloVault does not accept change-of-mind returns for minor condition differences or grading expectations.</p>
<p>If you have questions about a specific card, <a href="/pages/contact">contact us</a> with the Pokémon name, set, and card number before purchasing.</p>

<p>See our <a href="/pages/returns">Returns policy</a> for how we handle wrong items or damage in transit.</p>
